# Toronto Rising — Lua local function order (mandatory)

**This is the single most common class of runtime bugs in this repo** (~majority of “attempt to call a nil value” in TTS). Agents must treat it as a **pre-flight check on every Lua edit**, not an afterthought.

## The rule (one file = one chunk)

In **each** `.ttslua` file (and `core/global_script.ttslua`), every **`local function`** (or `local name` + later assignment) must appear **above** every caller in **that same file**:

- `function Global.*` / `Global.call` targets
- `function HUD_*`, `onObject*`, `onLoad`, coroutine entry names
- Other **`local function`** bodies in the same chunk

`require("core.foo")` does **not** share scope across files — fixing order in `npc_gameboard.ttslua` does not help `global_script.ttslua`.

## Why it fails silently in the editor

Lua 5.1 compiles each function body when the chunk loads. A call to `myHelper()` inside `function GlobalFoo()` where `myHelper` is declared **later** as `local function myHelper` resolves to **`_G.myHelper`**, which is usually **nil** → **`attempt to call a nil value`** at first use in-game (Save & Play), not at save time.

## Agent checklist (before marking Lua work done)

1. **List every new or moved `local function`** in the file you touched.
2. For each, **grep callers** in the same file (`myHelper(`) and confirm the definition line number is **less than** every caller line number — or use forward declare (below).
3. If you added a helper **near the bottom** of a large file (`core/npcs.ttslua`, `core/npc_gameboard_*.ttslua` siblings, `core/global_script.ttslua`), **stop** and move it up or forward-declare.
4. After Save & Play, exercise the path once (button, Apply, roll cancel, etc.) — nil-call bugs do not show in `npm run build`.

## Forward declaration (when order is awkward)

```lua
local resolveTokenSnapCatalogEntry
local isNpcSeatRowColumn

-- callers above ...

isNpcSeatRowColumn = function(col)
    -- ...
end

resolveTokenSnapCatalogEntry = function(board, token, fuzziness, config)
    -- ...
end
```

Use `local function foo` only when `foo` is defined **before** all callers. Otherwise: `local foo` at top + `foo = function(...)` later.

## Highest-risk files

| File | Risk |
| --- | --- |
| `core/global_script.ttslua` | Many `Global.*` entry points; helpers often appended at bottom |
| `core/npc_gameboard.ttslua` | Thin facade only; prefer editing the owning sibling |
| `core/npc_gameboard_snaps.ttslua` | Large catalog/install block |
| `core/npc_gameboard_reconcile.ttslua` | Scan/mirror/draft locals |
| `core/npc_gameboard_interactions.ttslua` | Drop/spread/group/dice-bag locals |
| `core/npc_gameboard_apply.ttslua` | Apply/Clear/Load locals |
| `core/npcs.ttslua` | `resolveNpcPlacementIntent` and other late-assigned locals |
| `core/lighting.ttslua`, `core/scenes.ttslua` | Large reconciler/helper blocks |

Prefer moving substantial logic into `require()` modules with a small ordered API instead of growing bottom-of-file locals in Global.

## Symptom → fix

| Console | Likely cause |
| --- | --- |
| `attempt to call a nil value` at `Global.call` / `GlobalGameboardApply` / HUD handler | Local helper defined **below** caller in same chunk |
| Stack shows `(local)` at a function name | That name was not in scope at compile time of the caller |

**Fix:** Move helper above caller, or forward-declare, then Save & Play.

